President of the United Nations General Assembly, María Fernanda Espinosa Garcés has arrived the Presidential Villa, Abuja for a meeting with President Muhammadu Buhari. Daily Trust reports that the UN GA president arrived the villa around 11:40 am, ahead of her meeting with President Buhari scheduled for 12noon. Ministers and other top government officials are expected to attend the meeting which is expected to last for 30 minutes. Just in: Buhari, security chiefs meet in Villa Buhari arrives New York for UN General Assembly 2017 budget: Buhari, Saraki in closed-door meeting Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin